oracle.mapviewer.share.stylex
Class RangedBucket

java.lang.Object
  oracle.mapviewer.share.stylex.Bucket
      oracle.mapviewer.share.stylex.RangedBucket
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public class RangedBucket
extends Bucket

Represents a range of values. A range starts at (including) a lower bound value, and covers all the possible values up to (but excluding) a upper bound value.

setRange

public void setRange(Field low,
                     Field high)
Sets the new lower and upper bound Field objects for this bucket's range. Mathematically the range is defined as [low, high). In other words, the low value is included in the bucket but the high value is not. If the lower bound is null, this bucket contains everything less than the upper bound; If the upper bound is null, this bucket contains everything equals to or greater than low.

Parameters:
low - - the lower bound Field object (inclusive)
high - - the upper bound Field object (exclusive)
